🎯 **LLM_Finetuning_CPU_Chatbot**

This repository documents the complete workflow and environment setup for fine-tuning a Large Language Model (LLM) on a CPU-based system, as part of the **Intel® Unnati Industrial Training on AI/ML**. The outcome was a **custom chatbot** built using the `meta-llama/Llama-2-7b-chat-hf` model, showcasing real-world LLM deployment under constrained hardware environments.

![Intel Chatbot Training](https://your-image-link-or-local-path/intel_llm_chatbot.png)

---

## 🛠️ Features Implemented

- **Fine-tuning** of LLaMA-2 model on local CPU using Hugging Face datasets.
- **Environment configuration** via Anaconda and `ipykernel` for local Jupyter execution.
- **Offline model access** using Git LFS for large-scale model cloning.
- **Custom chatbot deployment** with validation using Alpaca, CNN/DailyMail, and Evol-Codealpaca datasets.
- **Error resolution** for Hugging Face CLI and token authentication in restricted environments.

---

## 📁 Files and Components

| File/Folder                  | Description                                           |
|-----------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| `fine_tune_llm.ipynb`       | Main notebook for fine-tuning and inference           |
| `environment_setup.sh`      | Shell script to automate Conda and package setup      |
| `alpaca_dataset.zip`        | Cleaned dataset used for model training               |
| `chatbot_demo_video.mp4`    | Short demo of the deployed chatbot interaction        |
| `intel_llm_report.pdf`      | Final training report submitted to Intel              |

